{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": "# Summarization Quality Judge\n\nYou are evaluating the quality of session trace summarization from a coding-agent session.\n\n## Instructions\n\n1. Read the original trace file at: `evals/dataset/traces/claude_001.jsonl`\n2. Examine the summarization output below.\n3. Score on three dimensions (each 0.0 to 1.0):\n   - **completeness**: Does the summary capture the user's intent and what actually happened? Key actions, problems, and outcomes included? 1.0 = nothing important missed.\n   - **faithfulness**: Is the summary grounded in the trace? No hallucinated or invented details? 1.0 = perfectly faithful.\n   - **clarity**: Is the summary well-written, concise, and easy to understand? Good title and description? 1.0 = excellent clarity.\n4. Return ONLY valid JSON (no markdown fences, no extra text).\n\n## Summarization Output\n\n```json\n{\n  \"title\": \"Qwen3.5-4B-8bit Agentic Tool Calling with vllm-mlx\",\n  \"description\": \"Enabled and tested Qwen3.5 4B-8bit model for agentic tool calling in lerim benchmark, fixing vllm-mlx bugs and context size issues\",\n  \"user_intent\": \"Test whether smaller Qwen3.5 models (4B-8bit, 9B-8bit) can handle agentic workflows in lerim benchmark for extraction and summarization pipelines, finding more efficient alternatives to larger 35B model\",\n  \"session_narrative\": \"Explored vllm-mlx for serving Qwen3.5 models with tool calling. Discovered vllm-mlx has internal tool calling support (qwen3/hermes/llama parsers) but it wasn't exposed via CLI - created Python wrapper to programmatically enable it. Fixed critical bug in vllm-mlx 0.2.6 where MLLM.chat() and MLLM.stream_chat() didn't pass tools to get_chat_template(). Fixed Claude CLI judge nested session error by stripping CLAUDECODE env var. Tested 9B-8bit on agentic sync/maintain - failed due to token limits and parsing. Finally discovered 4B-8bit tool calling WORKS - lead agent successfully made 8 tool calls (704 tokens). Crash was due to trace size (355K tokens) exceeding 4B's 262K context window. Fixed by reducing max_window_tokens to 200K.\",\n  \"date\": \"2025-01-27\",\n  \"time\": \"00:00:00\",\n  \"coding_agent\": \"claude\",\n  \"raw_trace_path\": \"evals/dataset/traces/claude_001.jsonl\",\n  \"tags\": [\n    \"vllm-mlx\",\n    \"Qwen3.5\",\n    \"tool-calling\",\n    \"lerim-benchmark\",\n    \"4B-8bit\",\n    \"agentic-workflows\",\n    \"bugfix\"\n  ]\n}\n```\n\n## Response Format\n\nReturn exactly this JSON structure:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"completeness\": 0.0,\n  \"faithfulness\": 0.0,\n  \"clarity\": 0.0,\n  \"reasoning\": \"Brief explanation of scores.\"\n}\n```\n"}, "timestamp": "2026-03-07T09:21:34.947Z"}
